Wash and dry produce.

Quarter one @lime{1}(quartered) and set aside for serving; halve and juice remaining @lime{2}(juiced) into a #large bowl{}. Halve and juice @orange{1}(juiced) into bowl with lime juice. Peel and grate @garlic{6%cloves}(grated); add to same bowl and whisk to combine.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place between two large pieces of #plastic wrap{}. Pound with a #mallet{} or #rolling pin{} until chicken is about ½ inch thick. Season all over with half the @cumin{1%teaspoon}, half the @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. TIP: Press to adhere seasoning to chicken.

Add chicken to bowl with citrus marinade and turn to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and set aside to marinate. TIP: Wash your cutting board now or use a second one to finish prep in Step 3!

== Rice ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{3/4%cup}, @water{1 1/4%cups}, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Vegetables and Beans ==

While rice cooks, halve, core, and finely dice @bell pepper{1}(finely diced). Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @yellow onion{1}(finely diced); cut remaining onion into ½-inch wedges. Mince @cilantro{1/4%ounce}(minced).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a second small pot over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and diced onion; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add @black beans{1%can} and their liquid, half the @red wine vinegar{2 1/2%teaspoon}, and @water{1/2%cup}. Season with @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, remaining @cumin{1%teaspoon}, remaining @dried oregano{1%teaspoon}, @salt{1%tsp}, and pepper.

Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in half the cilantro. Remove from heat and keep covered until ready to serve.

== Chicken ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add chicken (letting any excess marinade drip off first) and onion wedges; cook until chicken is browned on one side and onion is softened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Reduce heat to medium-high and flip chicken; cook until chicken is cooked through and onion is browned, ~{3-5%minutes} more. TIP: Be sure to turn onion occasionally using #tongs{} while chicken cooks. If onion is done before chicken, transfer to a plate.

Transfer chicken to a #cutting board{}; let rest ~{1-2%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

Slice chicken crosswise.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; divide rice and chicken between shallow #bowls{}. Spoon beans over rice; top chicken with onion wedges. Garnish with remaining cilantro. Serve with lime wedges on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.